ce:section.ce:para:
The determination of PSA was performed with the fluorescence aptasensor based on FL-V2CTx. The fluorescence intensity increased with the increase of PSA concentration (Fig. 7
                        A). A good linear relationship was observed between ΔF and PSA concentration from 0.1 to 20 ng mL−1 (Fig. 7B). The linear equation was as follows: ΔF = 137.09 CPSA + 86.44 (R = 0.9991). The detection limit was 0.03 ng mL−1 (S/N = 3). We also compared this aptasensor with previous PSA fluorescence aptasensors [30–35] (Table 1
                        ), which showed that the proposed aptasensor had the lowest detection limit for PSA detection. Thus, the aptasensor based on aptamer-CGQDs as the fluorescence probe and FL-V2CTx as the quencher was superior.
